@page
@model DeveloperPortal.Pages.HelpModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Help";
}

<section id = "help-section" class = "container-fluid px-3 px-md-4 py-4" aria-labelledby="help-page-header">
    <h2 id="help-page-header">Help</h2>
    <div class="accordion" id="accordion-help">
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingOne">
                <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseOne">
                    What is the primary purpose of the Third Party Portal (TPP)?
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-bs-parent="#accordion-help">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    The TPP is a key digital initiative to improve the construction certification process managed by the Los Angeles Housing Department's (LAHD) Accessible Housing Program (ACHP) Construction Division. 
                    It serves as a central point for smooth interaction and secure document sharing between LAHD staff and external stakeholders like property developers, general contractors, architects, Certified Access Specialists (CASp), and Neutral Accessibility Consultants (NAC).
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingTwo">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                    What are the main objectives of the TPP project?
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-bs-parent="#accordion-help">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    The primary mission is to significantly streamline the construction certification process through a user-friendly, efficient, and secure digital platform. 
                    This includes facilitating the uploading, review, and approval of important construction documents, 
                    aiming to reduce project timelines and ensure compliance with legal requirements.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingThree">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
                    Who are the external parties involved in the TPP?
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingThree" data-bs-parent="#accordion-help">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    The external parties include Property Developers, General Contractors, Architects, Certified Access Specialists (CASp), and Neutral Accessibility Consultants (NAC).
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingFour">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFour">
                    What kind of documents are managed within the TPP?
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="collapseFour" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFour" data-bs-parent="#accordion-help">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    The TPP manages various documents such as Certified Access Specialists (CASp) reports, LAHD correspondence, regulatory agreements, project completion forms, 
                    Technical Submittal Reports (TSRs), backing documentation, design review plans and reports, certification documents, permit information (Certificate of Occupancy (CofO), 
                    Temporary Certificate of Occupancy (TCO), Building Permit), and Neutral Accessibility Consultants (NAC) reports.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingFive">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFive" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFive">
                    What is the general workflow for project submission in the TPP?
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="collapseFive" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFive" data-bs-parent="#accordion-help">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    The workflow includes creating a TPP account, linking the account to the ACHP project, submitting the project plan, and the RCS review process.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

